# Component Standards

## Structure

- UI primitives live under `src/components/ui/` (e.g. `button/`, `link/`, `popup/`, `icon/`).
- Page sections live under `src/components/pages/<page>/`.
- Layout chrome lives under `src/components/layout/`.
- Components are presentational and stateless unless interactivity is required.
- Use typed Astro props with safe defaults; expose behavior via explicit props (`variant`, `lang`, etc.).
- One responsibility per component; prefer composition with `Container`, `Flex`, `Stack`.

## Links (required)

- Do **not** use raw `<a>` in pages or feature components.
- Use `Link.astro` for anchors (`variant`: `default`, `social`, `toolbar`, `card`, `unstyled`).
- Use `SocialLink.astro` for icon-only social links.
- Use `Button.astro` with `href` for CTA-style navigation (it wraps `Link` internally).
- Set `external={false}` for internal routes; omit or set `external` for `http(s)` / new-tab behavior.

## Icons

- SVGs live in `src/assets/icons/` (descriptive names: `close.svg`, `github.svg`).
- Render via `Icon.astro` (`name` matches filename without extension).

## Styling (Tailwind-first)

**Default:** add and edit styles via Tailwind `class` strings using theme utilities (`bg-surface`, `text-text-muted`, `gap-4`, `md:p-5`, `transition-colors duration-150`).

### Do

- Use `surface` for bordered panels, or equivalent utilities on the element.
- Use semantic colors from theme (`text-primary`, `border-border`) — not `#hex` or `var(--color-primary)` in `.astro` files.
- Use `bg-gradient-to-br` for gradients (with `from-primary/10`, etc.).
- Include transition duration when adding hover/focus states (`duration-200 ease-in-out`).
- Keep `Card.astro`, `Button.astro`, `Link.astro`, `Typography.astro` as the source of variant styling.

### Do not

- Add new global CSS files or revive `components.css` / per-feature stylesheets for layout that utilities can handle.
- Use invalid utilities (`bg-linear-to-br`, `max-w-container`).
- Duplicate token values inline when a theme utility exists.
- Put long `<style>` blocks in main `.astro` files when Tailwind classes suffice.
- Keep legacy BEM class names (e.g. `services-section__grid`) unless a stylesheet or script selects them — prefer Tailwind utilities only.

### Custom CSS (exceptions only)

Use `ComponentName.styles.astro` with `<style is:global>` or `src/styles/motion.css` when Tailwind cannot:

- Keyframes and `prefers-reduced-motion`
- `dialog::backdrop`
- JS-driven animation (`--marquee-distance`, typewriter caret)
- `::after` content that must flip for RTL globally

Import at the bottom: `<ComponentNameStyles />` only when needed.

### Scripts

- If a component has **more than 10 lines** of `<script>`, split into `ComponentName.scripts.astro`.
- Import: `<ComponentNameScripts />` at the bottom of the main component.

## Accessibility

- Add `aria-label` / `aria-labelledby` on interactive and modal UI.
- Use semantic HTML (`nav`, `header`, `dialog`, `button` vs `div`).
